The experimental TAS spectra can be described by a sum of phonon terms on top of a flat background (BG). Each phonon is typically accounted for by a DHO68. The neutron spectra can then be described by the following expression:1I(Q,ω)=BG+1−exp−ℏωkbT−1 ∑j∣Fj(Q)∣2ωΓj(ω2−ωj2)2+(ωΓj)2,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
